@NODE Befehl " Commands"

	You can add the Commandstring this Parameter:
	
	- &d oder &D
	 the path will add to the String
	 
	 e.g. List &d list the dir which is specift in the Makefile

	- &a oder &A
	 at the start a window will open and ask for more parameter
	 (@{"Paramterwindow" LINK "Paramterfenster"})
	
	- &n oder &N
	 the name of the Project will insert (TO=...)
	
	- &l oder &L
	 the FROM=... statement will insert
	 
	 e.g BLink &L.o TO &N ->
	 BLINK MEMake.o MEMake.win.o TO MEMake
	 
	- &P
	 start the in the Module-Listview selectet Program,
	 without the test of Archivflag.
	
	- &p
	 start the in the Module-Listview selectet Program,
	 with the test of Archivflag is set.
	
	- &s
	 the FROM... statments are insert step by step
	 e.g. ASM &S ->
	 1. asm memake.s
	 2. asm memake.win.s
	 (with test of Archivflag is set)

	- &S
	 the FROM... statments are insert step by step
	 e.g. ASM &s ->
	 1. asm memake.s
	 2. asm memake.win.s
	 (without test of Archivflag is set)

	- &T
	 the FROM... statments are insert step by step
	 e.g. ASM &T ->
	 1. asm memake.s
	 2. asm memake.win.s
	 (with test of Archivflag is set and a test if the file exist )

	- &T
	 e.g. ASM &t ->
	 the FROM... statments are insert step by step
	 1. asm memake.s
	 2. asm memake.win.s
	 (without test of Archivflag is set and a test if the file exist )

@ENDNODE

