@NODE Makefile " Makefile"

	In the Makefile you can use follow key-words:

	- DIR=
		The Path of the Project
		e.g. DIR=DH2:Assembler/Quelltexte/MEMake
	- TO=
		Name of the Project, this sould be befor the FROM=
	- FROM=
		The Modules to the Project (sperated with a <;>)
	- OTHERS=
		other programs which displey in the modulelist
	- PREFS=
		prefs-file which sould load when this makefile is
		active

	Comments can add with ";" or "*" at the beginning of the line,
	this lines will be ignored.

	z.B:
	*
	* This is a Testproject
	*
	DIR=Quelltexte:Test/
	TO=Test
	FROM=Test;Test.win


@ENDNODE

