@NODE ARexx " ARexx-Port"

	MEMake has an small ARexx-Port, the Commands are:

	- Show:
	  shows the Main-Window
	- Hide:
	  hide all Windows
	- Quit:
	  quit the Program
	- LoadMake <Name.Make>:
	  load a new Makefile
	  (when you give no Path, the program will search
	   in the s: Directory) 
	- LoadPrefs <Name.Prefs>:
	  load a new Prefs-File
	  (when you give no Path, the program will search
	   in the s: Directory) 
	- Start <Name>:
	  start a Command (z.B. Start Linken)
	- Get <Number>:
	  give the name of the command with the <Number> back
	- STool <Name>:
	  start a Tool (z.B. Start SnoopDos)
	- GTool <Number>:
	  give the name of the tool with the <Number> back

	In the future there will be new Commands, like
	- Info: give Infos like the Infowindow back
	- Make: give the Modulelist back
	and you will lay ARexx-Script direct on the Buttons
	
@ENDNODE

